WEBVTT

00:15.995 --> 00:18.696
2
(PEOPLE CHATTER NOISILY)

00:18.796 --> 00:20.876
(DANCE MUSIC PUMPS
IN THE BACKGROUND)

00:23.716 --> 00:25.376
(EXPLOSION)

00:25.476 --> 00:27.796
(GLASS SHATTERS, DEBRIS FALLS)

00:30.756 --> 00:33.176
-(FLAMES ROAR)
-(MAN SCREAMS)

00:33.276 --> 00:36.157
(WOMAN CRIES)

00:38.077 --> 00:40.237
(HAUNTING MUSIC)

00:43.517 --> 00:47.557
Good and evil are villains.

00:49.997 --> 00:53.718
The world cannot have good
without the bad.

01:06.638 --> 01:09.839
But Bali,
nothing could happen here.

01:11.359 --> 01:13.759
This is a gentle island.

01:33.720 --> 01:35.340
I'm very sorry.

01:35.440 --> 01:39.080
What did we do wrong
to make the gods angry?

01:43.721 --> 01:46.161
(THEME MUSIC)

02:11.722 --> 02:13.762
(SOLEMN MUSIC)

02:28.963 --> 02:32.124
(APPLAUSE AND CHEERING)

02:36.284 --> 02:38.284
-(BRIDE LAUGHS)
-(CHEERING)

02:39.084 --> 02:41.024
Oh, wait, wait, wait, OK.

02:41.124 --> 02:42.944
-We love Bali.
-(LAUGHS)

02:43.044 --> 02:45.384
We adore the place.
Have you figured that out yet?

02:45.484 --> 02:46.984
(GUESTS LAUGH)

02:47.084 --> 02:49.745
Bali is where we met,
uh, where we fell in love.

02:49.845 --> 02:51.105
GUESTS: Awww!

02:51.205 --> 02:53.625
-Polly was so beautiful.
-Oh, was. Thanks, Dan.

02:53.725 --> 02:55.725
And still is. Still is.

02:56.325 --> 02:58.325
So beautiful.

02:59.525 --> 03:01.145
We shared our first kiss
in Bali.

03:01.245 --> 03:02.425
-Didn't we?
-Details!

03:02.525 --> 03:04.265
-No, you don't want details.
-WOMAN: Yes, we do!

03:04.365 --> 03:06.726
We so do! (LAUGHS)

03:09.526 --> 03:12.626
Details! Details! Details! Yeah!
(ALL JOIN IN) Details!

03:12.726 --> 03:15.466
-I kissed her.
-No, no, no, no, no.

03:15.566 --> 03:17.946
I kissed him
and that happened later.

03:18.046 --> 03:20.666
It did on the beach that night
when we went skinny-dipping.

03:20.766 --> 03:21.787
GUESTS: Ohhh!

03:21.887 --> 03:23.987
-But nothing else happened.
-Oh, sure!

03:24.087 --> 03:25.747
DAN: It didn't! It didn't!
It didn't!

03:25.847 --> 03:28.427
Really, this is what you come
up with in front of my boss?

03:28.527 --> 03:30.467
-More! More!
-DAN: It didn't. It didn't.

03:30.567 --> 03:31.947
POLLY: No, it's true. It didn't.

03:32.047 --> 03:33.547
DAN: And it didn't
because we both knew

03:33.647 --> 03:34.747
something special was happening.

03:34.847 --> 03:36.667
Normally when a player
on our team got drunk

03:36.767 --> 03:39.548
or hooked up with a girl, he'd
cop a fine from the captain.

03:39.648 --> 03:41.768
But...that time I didn't.

03:44.168 --> 03:46.268
Because the captain and everyone
else on the team could see

03:46.368 --> 03:48.368
that something special
was happening too.

03:49.928 --> 03:51.988
Bali is magical, isn't it, babe?

03:52.088 --> 03:53.988
Yeah. (CHUCKLES)

03:54.088 --> 03:55.669
(KISSES)

03:55.769 --> 03:57.509
And that's why we're going back.

03:57.609 --> 03:59.749
I know some of you are
joining us and you'll see.

03:59.849 --> 04:02.749
-Whoo-hoo!
-(GUESTS LAUGH)

04:02.849 --> 04:05.669
Bali is truly
the island of the gods.

04:05.769 --> 04:08.349
The most...beautiful land

04:08.449 --> 04:10.589
and the most gorgeous people
in the world.

04:10.689 --> 04:12.110
(GUESTS CLAP AND CHEER)

04:12.210 --> 04:14.430
-Do a toast. Do a toast.
-Oh, thank you.

04:14.530 --> 04:17.810
All be up standing
for Mr and Mrs Miller.

04:18.970 --> 04:21.950
ALL: Mr and Mrs Miller!

04:22.050 --> 04:24.050
(APPLAUSE AND CHEERING)

04:24.650 --> 04:26.030
To family.

04:26.130 --> 04:29.151
Congratulations
to my beautiful bride.

04:29.251 --> 04:31.251
Thank you, Mum.

04:37.051 --> 04:39.551
-Nic!
-(DOG BARKS IN THE DISTANCE)

04:39.651 --> 04:41.791
Nic, we're gonna miss
our flight.

04:41.891 --> 04:43.311
Jesus, Nat, keep your shirt on!

04:43.411 --> 04:45.712
-What, you're still packing?
-I'm packed. Get that one.

04:45.812 --> 04:46.872
It's empty.

04:46.972 --> 04:48.552
For shopping.

04:48.652 --> 04:51.452
Everything is so cheap, Nat.
You're not gonna believe it.

04:52.812 --> 04:54.512
NIC: Oh, see you, Mum.

04:54.612 --> 04:56.392
I'll call you from Bali.
Love you!

04:56.492 --> 04:58.112
-'Bye!
-MOTHER: 'Bye, Natalie.

04:58.212 --> 05:00.072
-'Bye, Nicole.
-(HORN HONKS)

05:00.172 --> 05:02.153
-If we miss our flight...
-We're not gonna miss it.

05:02.253 --> 05:04.613
Hey, is that Luke Beasley?

05:05.813 --> 05:08.113
-NICOLE: Put this in the cab.
-What's he doing here?

05:08.213 --> 05:09.633
-Shut up.
-Oh, he's smiling.

05:09.733 --> 05:12.033
-Not a word. Go! Go!
-(CHUCKLES)

05:12.133 --> 05:13.233
-Bonjour!
-Bonjour.

05:13.333 --> 05:14.753
-Hey.
-Hey.

05:14.853 --> 05:16.393
-What are you doing here?
-Um...

05:16.493 --> 05:18.513
You dropped these last night.

05:18.613 --> 05:20.514
Just thought
you might want them.

05:20.614 --> 05:22.614
(CAR BOOT SHUTS)

05:24.174 --> 05:26.074
-I'm gonna miss you.
-(CAR DOOR SHUTS)

05:26.174 --> 05:29.414
It's only two weeks.
You'll survive, mate.

05:33.374 --> 05:34.674
'Bye, Luke.

05:34.774 --> 05:36.595
I'm just going to Bali. (LAUGHS)

05:36.695 --> 05:38.695
(CAR ENGINE STARTS)

05:39.495 --> 05:41.495
(CAR DRIVES AWAY)

06:12.457 --> 06:14.457
OK?

06:35.498 --> 06:37.498
OK?

06:40.378 --> 06:42.378
OK?

06:44.139 --> 06:46.139
OK.

07:18.501 --> 07:20.621
Allahu Akbar.

07:24.181 --> 07:26.781
Allahu Akbar.

07:29.981 --> 07:32.461
Allahu Akbar.

07:41.622 --> 07:43.622
Wisnu.

07:49.783 --> 07:51.783
(CHATTER)

07:58.743 --> 08:01.243
DAN: Polly, see anything
you like, I'll buy it.

08:01.343 --> 08:03.543
POLLY: What about
one of those?

08:05.623 --> 08:07.684
-Oh, there's, like, mini ones.
-Yeah.

08:07.784 --> 08:09.784
DAN: Oh, beautiful.

08:10.424 --> 08:11.964
-(PHONE RINGS)
-Oh, you're not answering that.

08:12.064 --> 08:13.724
-Oh, but it could be work.
-Exactly.

08:13.824 --> 08:15.164
Come on. Let go.

08:15.264 --> 08:17.324
DAN: Will you tell her?
Will you tell her?

08:17.424 --> 08:19.124
-(PHONE RINGS)
-Oh, come on, Pol, put it away.

08:19.224 --> 08:20.924
-It'll just be a second.
-We're on our honeymoon.

08:21.024 --> 08:22.084
We're not working.

08:22.184 --> 08:23.445
Polly, you invited us here,
remember?

08:23.545 --> 08:25.645
We didn't come all this way
just to watch you work.

08:25.745 --> 08:27.365
-Alright. OK.
-Yeah? Got the note?

08:27.465 --> 08:29.645
-Yeah.
-Good.

08:29.745 --> 08:31.485
DAN: You've already got that one
I think, anyway.

08:31.585 --> 08:32.485
(PHONE RINGS)

08:32.585 --> 08:34.005
Hi. Yeah.

08:34.105 --> 08:36.645
It's 60,000 shares
of CRX Mining at $8.

08:36.745 --> 08:39.365
That's what we agreed to.
No, not 7.6 or 7...

08:39.465 --> 08:42.086
-Oh, my Christ.
-You promised.

08:42.186 --> 08:44.186
I did.

08:45.066 --> 08:45.966
Thank you.

08:46.066 --> 08:48.526
Hey, guys, guys.
How do we look?

08:48.626 --> 08:50.526
POLLY: Like four pointy heads.

08:50.626 --> 08:52.806
-And then there were five.
-Four gorgeous pointy heads.

08:52.906 --> 08:54.086
ANNIKA: Photo!
James, take a photo.

08:54.186 --> 08:56.206
JAMES: Yeah, photo! Photo!

08:56.306 --> 08:58.727
Everyone gather round.
Crowd in, crowd in. Get her in.

08:58.827 --> 09:00.407
-POLLY: Fine, fine, fine, James.
-OK, you ready?

09:00.507 --> 09:01.967
I'm warning you.
I'll destroy those negatives.

09:02.067 --> 09:03.887
I promise they'll be good.
It's gonna be great.

09:03.987 --> 09:05.487
Everyone, just do
your most gorgeous faces.

09:05.587 --> 09:07.087
Dan, I know
this'll be hard for you.

09:07.187 --> 09:09.727
-I'm doing my best.
-Here we go! Smile!

09:09.827 --> 09:11.007
Say Polly!

09:11.107 --> 09:12.967
-ALL: Polly!
-JAMES: Beautiful.

09:13.067 --> 09:14.368
-Jimmy, take the pic.
-Yep.

09:14.468 --> 09:15.848
You coming to the Sari Club?

09:15.948 --> 09:17.848
I'm having dinner first,
but I'll be there late.

09:17.948 --> 09:19.368
OK, I want one more picture.

09:19.468 --> 09:21.168
-On three, hats in the air.
-DAN: Great.

09:21.268 --> 09:22.928
OK? One, two, three!

09:23.028 --> 09:25.028
ALL: Bali!

09:28.268 --> 09:31.749
(PEOPLE SHOUT,
HORNS HONK CONSTANTLY)

09:32.749 --> 09:34.409
-Oh. Sorry. (LAUGHS)
-(LAUGHS)

09:34.509 --> 09:37.049
Didn't I tell you you'd love
this place? Didn't I tell you?

09:37.149 --> 09:38.889
-No, thank you.
-Thank you.

09:38.989 --> 09:40.689
MAN: Whoo!

09:40.789 --> 09:43.129
-How much? 10?
-10, mate. You know it.

09:43.229 --> 09:44.369
There's 10.

09:44.469 --> 09:46.169
How's that heat?

09:46.269 --> 09:48.510
Mate, I love it. Nah.

09:51.350 --> 09:52.570
Oh.

09:52.670 --> 09:55.250
-It smells so good!
-Oh, let's go back and get some.

09:55.350 --> 09:56.890
-(PAN SIZZLES)
-LOCAL MAN: Mister, mister.

09:56.990 --> 09:59.690
-Feels like beer o'clock.
-Yep.

09:59.790 --> 10:01.250
I just gotta call Nerissa first.

10:01.350 --> 10:04.051
-What for?
-She didn't want me to come.

10:04.151 --> 10:05.691
-(CAR BOOT SHUTS)
-You on a leash, mate?

10:05.791 --> 10:07.051
(LAUGHS) Long leash.

10:07.151 --> 10:09.051
NATALIE: Nick, it's Jason
McCartney and Mick Martyn.

10:09.151 --> 10:10.891
The football players.
North Melbourne.

10:10.991 --> 10:13.051
-Just don't be embarrassing, OK?
-OK. Sorry.

10:13.151 --> 10:15.171
-Just be cool. Be cool.
-Be cool. Yeah, I'm cool.

10:15.271 --> 10:16.531
-You're cool.
-I am cool.

10:16.631 --> 10:19.131
Oi, Jason! Go the Roos!

10:19.231 --> 10:21.772
-(JASON CHUCKLES) Yeah.
-NATALIE: Ohh!

10:21.872 --> 10:23.932
Wow. I'm embarrassing.

10:24.032 --> 10:25.452
(NICOLE LAUGHS)

10:25.552 --> 10:27.612
Nic, you loser.

10:27.712 --> 10:30.892
-Alright, let's go check in.
-Yeah, alright.

10:30.992 --> 10:33.152
(HORN HONKS)

10:41.073 --> 10:44.913
(BABY GURGLES)

11:15.315 --> 11:17.315
No.

11:52.997 --> 11:54.737
(PAN SIZZLES)

11:54.837 --> 11:56.617
(MAN LAUGHS)

11:56.717 --> 12:00.117
Oh. (MUTTERS IN LOCAL LANGUAGE)

12:09.118 --> 12:11.118
WOMAN:

12:12.278 --> 12:14.278
You must learn the English.

12:19.519 --> 12:22.299
You must practise for work.

12:22.399 --> 12:25.859
Hello! Goodbye! Bugger off.

12:25.959 --> 12:27.959
That's all the English I need.

12:34.439 --> 12:36.440
(ROOSTER CROWS)

12:37.720 --> 12:40.180
-(BIRDSONG)
-Can you believe we did it?

12:40.280 --> 12:42.260
-We did.
-Married.

12:42.360 --> 12:44.360
-I know.
-(LAUGHS)

12:45.040 --> 12:49.760
And do you know...you have
six-inch beauty, Mrs Miller.

12:51.000 --> 12:52.341
What?

12:52.441 --> 12:53.861
This,

12:53.961 --> 12:55.961
right here.

12:56.441 --> 12:58.901
From six inches,
you're beautiful.

12:59.001 --> 13:00.941
Ah, so from the other side
of the room

13:01.041 --> 13:03.261
I look like
Camilla Parker Bowles?

13:03.361 --> 13:05.861
-Let me see.
-You bastard! (LAUGHS)

13:05.961 --> 13:07.621
No, you're still pretty fair
from back here.

13:07.721 --> 13:09.662
-I'll give you 'pretty fair'!
-(PHONE BEEPS)

13:09.762 --> 13:11.062
Don't!

13:11.162 --> 13:13.162
Of course not.

13:14.002 --> 13:16.002
Do me a favour, then.
Close your eyes.

13:19.842 --> 13:22.362
-(PHONE BEEPS)
-DAN: I could hear that.

13:26.803 --> 13:28.803
How much time do we have?

13:37.883 --> 13:40.323
(LOUD DANCE MUSIC)

13:48.364 --> 13:51.224
-Oh!
-(LAUGHS)

13:51.324 --> 13:53.904
-Hughsie. Good to see you.
-Good to see you too, mate.

13:54.004 --> 13:56.104
Jase is coming down. He's
on the phone with the missus.

13:56.204 --> 13:57.904
-Yeah, no worries, bro.
-How are you, mate?

13:58.004 --> 13:59.345
Yeah, good. Yeah.

13:59.445 --> 14:02.205
(LOUD DANCE MUSIC PUMPS)

14:07.685 --> 14:09.785
Whoo!

14:09.885 --> 14:11.745
Ahh. Are we going surfing?

14:11.845 --> 14:14.985
Yeah, nah. Later on, though.
First we party, hey?

14:15.085 --> 14:17.566
-(LAUGHS)
-(DANCE MUSIC PUMPS)

14:20.046 --> 14:22.026
Whoo!

14:22.126 --> 14:25.026
Look at them all.
It's like a smorgasbord.

14:25.126 --> 14:28.106
We should get these boys to line
up and we can take our pick.

14:28.206 --> 14:29.586
Oh, my gosh! Shut up.

14:29.686 --> 14:31.686
(SCREAMS)

14:32.607 --> 14:34.307
(DANCE MUSIC FADES)

14:34.407 --> 14:38.087
(WOMAN SINGS IN LOCAL LANGUAGE)

14:42.047 --> 14:44.087
(WOMAN CONTINUES SINGING)

15:22.289 --> 15:24.610
(WOMAN CONTINUES SINGING)

15:29.490 --> 15:31.770
(CONTINUES SINGING)

15:56.892 --> 15:59.252
(WOMAN HUMS)

16:12.172 --> 16:13.273
(FOOTSTEPS)

16:13.373 --> 16:15.233
Hey, what you doing?

16:15.333 --> 16:17.333
Are you gonna get changed?

16:18.173 --> 16:21.013
It's so nice here.
I'm just relaxing.

16:22.013 --> 16:24.833
Well, get un-relaxed.
We're going out.

16:24.933 --> 16:28.233
Hmm. Don't you wanna just
sit back and soak it all in?

16:28.333 --> 16:31.234
Yeah. At a nightclub.

16:31.334 --> 16:33.834
Come on, it's my first night
in Bali. Don't do this to me.

16:33.934 --> 16:35.194
We've got two weeks here.

16:35.294 --> 16:38.334
Yeah, two weeks of drinking,
dancing and shopping.

16:39.334 --> 16:42.034
-Your words, not mine.
-OK, OK.

16:42.134 --> 16:43.234
Yay!

16:43.334 --> 16:45.034
-(NICOLE LAUGHS)
-So where should we go?

16:45.134 --> 16:48.035
Uh, Sari Club is THE place, but
let's go drink at Paddy's first.

16:48.135 --> 16:50.395
-It's just across the road.
-Great.

16:50.495 --> 16:51.875
So what's the real reason

16:51.975 --> 16:53.475
that Luke was at your place
this morning?

16:53.575 --> 16:55.875
I told you! He was dropping off
my sunglasses.

16:55.975 --> 16:57.975
Why did he have them?

16:58.575 --> 17:00.795
(LAUGHS) We had a moment.

17:00.895 --> 17:02.515
-Oh?
-Last night.

17:02.615 --> 17:04.476
Outside a church! (LAUGHS)

17:04.576 --> 17:06.556
Yeah, that's...hot.

17:06.656 --> 17:08.916
Mmm! It was. (LAUGHS)

17:09.016 --> 17:11.116
No, it was nice.

17:11.216 --> 17:12.796
He told me he loves me.

17:12.896 --> 17:13.996
No?!

17:14.096 --> 17:15.196
Yep. (CHUCKLES)

17:15.296 --> 17:17.156
Oh, my God.
What did you say back?

17:17.256 --> 17:19.236
Um...I said OK.

17:19.336 --> 17:20.877
(BOTH LAUGH)

17:20.977 --> 17:24.057
(DANCE MUSIC PUMPS)

17:25.737 --> 17:27.737
(HORN HONKS)

17:31.457 --> 17:33.397
(DANCE MUSIC CONTINUES)

17:33.497 --> 17:37.038
♪ You're the music
in my soul... ♪

17:37.138 --> 17:40.398
If you want to change dollar
for rupiah, you come to me, OK?

17:40.498 --> 17:43.018
Gede. Give you best price.

17:45.898 --> 17:47.638
(PEOPLE LAUGH)

17:47.738 --> 17:49.838
OK, OK. Alright, no, no, no.
We're gonna do shots.

17:49.938 --> 17:52.038
Everyone's gonna do
maybe two or three

17:52.138 --> 17:54.439
and then we're going to murder
the dance floor!

17:54.539 --> 17:56.539
(LAUGHS)

17:57.339 --> 17:59.779
Another beer.

18:01.019 --> 18:02.479
And one more.

18:02.579 --> 18:04.319
WOMAN: I know. I know.

18:04.419 --> 18:06.079
DAN: OK, drink.
Come on, here we go.

18:06.179 --> 18:09.279
-POLLY: No, don't. Don't.
-OTHERS: Down! Down! Down! Down!

18:09.379 --> 18:12.480
-Come on, let's dance.
-Yeah, be my guest.

18:12.580 --> 18:14.520
You gotta dance now.

18:14.620 --> 18:16.440
Will you get me another beer?

18:16.540 --> 18:17.920
-A beer?
-Get me a beer.

18:18.020 --> 18:19.880
Yeah, get him a beer.

18:19.980 --> 18:21.280
♪ So, come on

18:21.380 --> 18:23.000
♪ Come on

18:23.100 --> 18:26.520
♪ Let's dance... ♪

18:26.620 --> 18:29.281
Sorry. Thank you.

18:29.381 --> 18:31.321
Excuse me, sorry,
I don't mean to push but...

18:31.421 --> 18:33.401
-Beer?
-Desperate for it.

18:33.501 --> 18:35.721
-It's a nice place, eh?
-Yeah, it's fab.

18:35.821 --> 18:37.601
You a Pom?

18:37.701 --> 18:40.081
-Afraid so.
-(LAUGHS)

18:40.181 --> 18:42.161
Nah, it's not your fault.
Don't worry about it.

18:42.261 --> 18:44.042
Can we get, um, two beers,
please?

18:44.142 --> 18:46.522
Thank you.
Are you guys doing shots?

18:46.622 --> 18:48.362
-Nah, but he is.
-You guys go ahead.

18:48.462 --> 18:50.482
-Hey, mate, it's your turn!
-I can't do shots.

18:50.582 --> 18:51.842
That is disgusting!

18:51.942 --> 18:54.722
(LAUGHS) Thank you, mate.
Appreciate it.

18:54.822 --> 18:56.482
-POLLY: Thank you.
-Cheers, love.

18:56.582 --> 18:57.602
Thanks, babe.

18:57.702 --> 19:00.582
♪ You fill my soul

19:01.583 --> 19:03.283
♪ You're the music

19:03.383 --> 19:05.123
♪ You're the joy

19:05.223 --> 19:07.223
♪ Every girl... ♪

19:15.543 --> 19:17.544
(INHALES, THEN EXHALES)

19:23.784 --> 19:26.384
(HORNS HONK)

19:32.104 --> 19:34.144
(DANCE MUSIC PUMPS)

19:37.505 --> 19:39.645
Sorry.

19:39.745 --> 19:41.085
NATALIE: My God.

19:41.185 --> 19:43.185
(NICOLE LAUGHS)

19:45.305 --> 19:49.165
♪ I do my fist pump, pump,
pump, pump, pump, pump

19:49.265 --> 19:52.606
♪ Then I jump, jump, jump,
jump, jump, jump, jump

19:52.706 --> 19:56.246
♪ I do my fist pump, pump,
pump, pump, pump, pump

19:56.346 --> 20:00.486
♪ Then I jump, jump, jump,
jump, jump, jump, jump

20:00.586 --> 20:02.366
♪ Get up
Get on the floor now

20:02.466 --> 20:04.006
♪ DJ, throw it on now... ♪

20:04.106 --> 20:06.206
-Do you want to do a shot?
-We just got here.

20:06.306 --> 20:08.487
